    <edge source="VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN" target="ISOLATION ROOM">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d8">ISOLATION ROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">APPLIED_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Ventilation system design controls are specifically applied in isolation rooms to reduce airborne pathogen exposure by optimizing airflow and contaminant transport paths.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN" target="AIRBORNE INFECTIOUS DISEASE AGENTS">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE INFECTIOUS DISEASE AGENTS</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">Ventilation system design targets airborne infectious disease agents by controlling airflow and contaminant transport to reduce exposure and infection risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN" target="AIR CHANGES PER HOUR">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d8">AIR CHANGES PER HOUR</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DOSE</data>
      <data key="d10">Ventilation system design considers air changes per hour (ACH) as a quantitative parameter, but aims to reduce infection risk primarily through airflow path optimization rather than increasing ACH.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN" target="VENTILATION EFFECTIVENESS">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d8">VENTILATION EFFECTIVENESS</data>
      <data key="d9">OUTPERFORMS</data>
      <data key="d10">Ventilation system design aims to improve ventilation effectiveness by optimizing contaminant transport paths, which is more impactful than simply increasing air changes per hour.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN" target="PATIENT ROOM">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d8">PATIENT ROOM</data>
      <data key="d9">APPLIED_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Ventilation system design is implemented in patient rooms to control airborne contaminant transmission by optimizing airflow pathways, thereby reducing infection risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN" target="AIR CHANGE RATE (ACH)">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d8">AIR CHANGE RATE (ACH)</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DOSE</data>
      <data key="d10">Ventilation system design operates with an air change rate (ACH) parameter that quantifies the airflow rate; however, adherence to the hypothesized airflow path principle may have a greater impact on reducing airborne pathogen transmission than ACH alone.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="COMPUTATIONAL FLUID DYNAMICS ANALYSIS" target="VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN">
      <data key="d7">COMPUTATIONAL FLUID DYNAMICS ANALYSIS</data>
      <data key="d8">VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The ventilation system design is supported and validated by computational fluid dynamics analysis examining contaminant transport and control strategies.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIRFLOW PATH" target="CONTAMINANT SOURCE">
      <data key="d7">AIRFLOW PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">CONTAMINANT SOURCE</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">The airflow path is designed to target and capture contaminants emitted from the contaminant source, facilitating their removal and reducing exposure risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_3</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIRFLOW PATH" target="VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN">
      <data key="d7">AIRFLOW PATH</data>
      <data key="d8">VENTILATION SYSTEM DESIGN</data>
      <data key="d9">COMPLEMENTS</data>
      <data key="d10">The airflow path is a critical component that complements ventilation system design by ensuring an uninterrupted route for contaminant removal.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_3</data>
